uest</span><hr size=1> Well, I've experimented a lot around the different realms, trying to find my niche, so far my favorites in Albion are my cleric and my scout, but I have noticed a bit of a gap in our ranks that I'm thinking about experimenting with filling. We don't have a single sorcerer. I'm trying to figure out why this is. I know that they are fearsome soloers, and would seem to be very handy as crowd control in dungeons, but how useful are they in RvR? Sorcerers seem to me to be one to the least played classes in Albion. Any ideas why? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/ugamlaen0.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gamlaen0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(10/29/01 4:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sorcerer info request</span><hr size=1> Hey Aldric...<br>
<br>
Warcry has an excellent Sorcercer guide...I too have looked at the class to a degree, but decided on some others within Albion to play as 'secondaries&quot;.  One of the things to consider in RvR with regards to Sorcerers is that you can't &quot;charm&quot; someone on the other side.  Charming is one of the primary strengths of the sorcerers...and for that matter minstrels...but Mythic is still working through it in regards to RvR...so I guess to answer your question...play the sorcerer for it's solo potential, but play it with reservation in regards to it's PvP (RvR) aspects at the moment as no one knows how it will turn out in the end.  I do believe Mez does impact your opponent in RvR...but the problem there is one of expediency...if you mez an opponent..chances are it will be broken in short order in the general &quot;scrum&quot; that is the melee that is taking place...and the range is much shorter than bows so you can't really effectively get to the archer/caster line either...Just my impression, but it is certainly a great solo and even great group class in PvE. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/ugamlaen0.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gamlaen0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(10/29/01 4:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sorcerer info request</span><hr size=1> Aldric, here is the link to the sorcerer guide I mentioned.<br>
